results.title: Penetrator for Commodore 64
results.material_description: Cassette tape computer game. Cassette & cover in clear plastic cassette case
results.brief_description:
Penetrator is a side scrolling shooter for one or two players for the Commodore 64. The player flies a fighter across the screen from left to right, dodging terrain and enemy shots and shooting enemy structures. Players can accelerate and brake their fighter but prolonged braking can stall it. Enemies become more accurate the longer the player is exposed to the radar and the danger level is shown on the player’s console. The game can also be customised for landscape and the number and positions of enemy missile and radar bases.

Original game developed by Beam Software for Commodore 64, published in 1982 by Melbourne House

Original game created for Commodore 64 by Matthew Hall and released into the public domain circa 1985. More info on Matt Hall’s games can be found at: http://www.ourdigitalheritage.org/archive/playitagain/bedroom-coders-matthew-hall-15-commodore-64-games-rescued-from-decaying-cassettes/

results.title: Emulation of Operation Tiger Force for Commodore 64
results.brief_description:
Operation Tigerforce is a single player action game set in a hostile warzone. Using the joystick, the player moves and shoots at both mobile and stationary enemies from a top-down perspective. Most enemies take several shots to defeat and will add to the player’s overall score. Getting hit by enemy bullets or touching an enemy will cost the player a life. The player is initally given two extra lives. Losing both will restart the game. There is a lengthy initial load time.
Original game created for Commodore 64 by Matthew Hall and released into the public domain circa 1985. More info on Matt Hall’s games can be found at: http://www.ourdigitalheritage.org/archive/playitagain/bedroom-coders-matthew-hall-15-commodore-64-games-rescued-from-decaying-cassettes/

Lightraycer is a two player arcade game modelled on TRON. Much like TRON, both players try to get the longest snake possible without hitting the walls, themselves or the other player. The red player has the following movement controls: “W” for up. “A” for left. “S” for right. “Z” for down. Blue player may also have separate set of controls but it may require a full C-64 keyboard.

results.brief_description:
Ladder Invaders II is a single player arcade game, The player is the middle purple figure and can move up using “S” and down using “X” on a horizontal ladder. Two ladders on the left and right of the player have green figures scaling up. The player must fire on them using “RETURN” to prevent them from reaching the top of their ladder. The laser the player fires goes both left and right and hits all ladders. Once 3 green figures reaches the top, the player loses. The laser also removes the orange background but has not noticable effect on gameplay.

results.brief_description: Knuckle Busters [computer game]. Knuckle Busters is a single player side scrolling action platformer. Players take on the role of Deke, a criminal escaping from a prision facility. Due to Deke’s tampering with the Central Computer, the facility and the city are expected to blow up, thus putting a time limit on the players. Players can jump and drop from platforms, avoid or fight androids, collect items and health from barrels and open doors. Deke’s condition is displayed to the player on a pop up menu including lives left, score, time count down, energy level and current object carried.

results.brief_description: Judge Dredd [computer game]. Judge Dredd is a single player action platformer. Players move Dredd to locations of crime as they appear on the sector map and select the crime they wish to pass judgement on. Once a crime has been selected, Dredd is dropped into a side scrolling platformer where both perps and civilians roam. Each crime is given an appropriate response level of Halt, Warn and Kill, though it is up to player discretion to change the response level. Depending on the response level is the action Dredd can perform, either shouting halt, firing warning shots or firing real bullets. Dredd can select a type of bullet from normal, armour piercing, incendiary, ricochet, high explosive and heat seeking.
